Pre-Account Takeover

Pre-account takeover takes place when an attacker registers to the client application using victims’ email, prior to victim registering himself with the application. To test if the OAuth flow is vulnerable to this, the below steps can be followed:-

    Attacker creates an account using the normal signup process using the victim’s email address before the victim has registered on the client application
    The attacker would be asked to verify the email address
    The victim tries to register using a different signup method with the same email address using the OAuth flow.
    The victim logs into the client application which bypasses the email verification step for the attacker.
    The attacker would be able to log in as the victim and read all the data that has been added by the victim by using the victim’s email address and the attacker’s password .

In this scenario just by knowing the email address, the attacker can take over the victim’s account completely without the victim’s knowledge. While creating a new account proper email validation should be done. Users should not be allowed to create a new account if already another account with the same email id has been created.

